biogHists.text: Joseph Warrington was a New Jersey Quaker. He was born to Henry Warrington and Elizabeth Bishop on April 20th, 1730 (old style), along with a twin brother named Benjamin. Warrington married Rebecca Walton in 1768, and died in April 1803.

relations.note: Joseph Warrington was the brother of Hannah Warrington, Joseph Buzby's wife.

relations.content: Evesham Monthly Meeting (Society of Friends : 1760-1827 : Mount Laurel, N.J.)

relations.note: Joseph Warrington was the brother Esther Warrington, John Hunt's wife.
Joseph Warrington was the brother of Sarah Warrington, William Rogers's first wife.
Joseph Warrington was the brother of Rachel Warrington, Aaron Wills's wife.

resource.title: John Hunt papers, 1770-1828.
resource.abstract: John Hunt kept a diary for more than 40 years, recording Quaker concerns and daily events. This collections consists primarily of the manuscript journal, 1770-1800; fragments of 1805, 1806 & 1808; and 1814-1824. Of particular interest are the visits of prominent Quakers, including Elias Hicks and Jonathan Evans. There is also an account book, some correspondence received, and other miscellaneous materials. Correspondents include Ann R. Matlack, Asa Matlack, Elizabeth A. Lippincott, John Cox, Joseph Foulke, and Josiah Roberts.
